headline: Auto Tariffs Add $2,000 to New Car Prices
summary: New tariffs are increasing car prices by nearly $2,000 per vehicle, impacting consumer sales and shifting the outlook for electric vehicle adoption in the US.

headline: General Motors (GM): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Over the last six months, General Motors’s shares have sunk to $49, producing a disappointing 8.4% loss while the S&P 500 was flat. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
